Configure AWS CLI:
Open your terminal or command prompt.
Run the following command to configure your AWS CLI:
aws configure

Enter your AWS Access Key ID, Secret Access Key, region, and output format when prompted.
Create a directory for your Terraform configuration:
Run the following commands to create a directory and navigate into it:
mkdir terraform_project
cd terraform_project

Create a main.tf file:
Inside the terraform_project directory, create a file named main.tf and open it in your preferred text editor.
Copy and paste the following code into main.tf:

terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 4.16"
    }
  }
  required_version = ">= 1.2.0"
}

provider "aws" {
  region  = "us-west-2"
}

resource "aws_instance" "app_server" {
  ami           = "ami-830c94e3"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"

  tags = {
    Name = "Terraform_Demo"
  }
}

Initialize Terraform:
Run the following command to initialize Terraform:
terraform init

Plan the Terraform deployment:
Run the following command to create an execution plan:
terraform plan

Apply the Terraform configuration:
Run the following command to apply the configuration:
terraform apply

When prompted, type yes to confirm the deployment.
